articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The statement came after Israeli specialists said that one of the four bodies handed over by Hamas was an unidentified woman and not hostage Shiri Bibas.
articles.title: Israeli PM Netanyahu says Hamas will pay for not returning Shiri Bibas

articles.author: John Geddie, Tim Kelly, David Brunnstrom
articles.description: When President Donald Trump sat down to lunch with his Japanese counterpart this month, talk turned quickly to how Tokyo could help realise a decades-old proposal to unlock gas in Alaska and ship it to U.S. allies in Asia.
articles.title: Trump seeks to reshape Asia's energy supplies with US gas

articles.author: Olena Harmash, Tom Balmforth
articles.description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskiy said he was counting on Ukrainian and European unity and U.S. pragmatism as Kyiv faces a mounting crisis in relations with its hitherto key U.S. ally.
articles.title: Zelenskiy calls for US pragmatism after Trump calls him a 'dictator'

articles.author: Antoni Slodkowski, Laurie Chen
articles.description: For the last three years, China has repeatedly signalled a willingness to act as a peacemaker in the war in Ukraine.
articles.title: China's hopes to be Ukraine peacemaker collide with its goals on Trump, trade

articles.description: But Arab states have yet to tackle critical issues like who will foot the bill for Gaza's reconstruction or how the Strip will be governed.
articles.title: Arab states scramble to counter Trump's Gaza 'Riviera' plan

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: South Korean police are formally building a case against impeached President Yoon Suk Yeol over accusations he obstructed the execution of an arrest warrant, a police spokesperson said on Friday.
articles.title: South Korea police say building case against Yoon for obstructing arrest

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Sweden is investigating a possible breach of an undersea cable off the country's southwestern coast in the Baltic Sea, the coastguard said on Friday, in an area where multiple seabed cables have been damaged in recent months.
articles.title: Sweden investigates possible breach of Baltic Sea cable

articles.author: Kirsty Needham, Lucy Craymer
articles.description: Australia expressed concern to China on Friday over the short notice given by the Chinese navy that it would hold a live-fire exercise in international waters between Australia and New Zealand, forcing airlines to divert flights, Defence Minister Richard Marles said.
articles.title: Airlines warned as Chinese navy holds live-fire exercises off Australia

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Defence will remain a top budget priority for Poland, Finance Minister Andrzej Domanski said on Friday, urging European Union countries to back a Polish proposal that would let them hike military spending without breaking the bloc's fiscal rules.
articles.title: Defence spending will remain top priority for Poland, says finance minister

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The European Commission will propose boosting surveillance of undersea cables and establishing a fleet of vessels available to repair cables in emergencies, it said in an action plan published Friday.
articles.title: EU will propose establishing fleet of vessels for emergency undersea cable repairs
